What happened ? The owners of a condominium building at 200 Riverside Boulevard in New York City have been fighting in court for the right to remove the word " Trump " from its prominent place in big gold letters from the front of their building . President Donald Trump never owned the building in question . Nor did any company that he controlled or owned a stake in . Instead , the name " Trump Place " was emblazoned on the side of the building as part of a March 2000 licensing deal . Under the guidelines of the deal , the owners of the building would pay Trump a grand total of $ 1 in exchange for being able to advertise the Trump name on the building forever . Lawyers for] …
